   09-06-2012 08:32 PM

   I had similar issues even know I had a detailed format in which she
   should follow while my grand daughter was in school.She was newly
   diagnosed just last march,and she was the first student in that school
   with type 1 for the past 3 years.The nurse had to brush up on the
   information ,and I would get these calls that she had high B/S numbers
   and she asked me what to do,at that time I would tell her to dose her
   for it per what the sheet says,she would tell me the sheet dont specify
   how and when and how much to give her...as most of you know with
   children in school ,the sheet and medical paperwork is very precise and
   complete with all instructions that anyone in the medical field should
   be able to take care of...her answer was to sit her in the office and
   have her drink water and check her every 15 mins until she came down,I
   asked if this is the remedy then why the need for insulin to begin
   with.....I got tired of foolin with her and just would go pick my GD up
   from school beings it was the ending of the school year
   anyway......When I kooled down I had to go into the office and talk
   with the nurse and explain what exactly the med sheet was saying,she
   then understtod and I didnt really have as much problems after
   that....communication is the key here,if i couldnt communicate with GD
   school nurse and vice versa the only one suffering would be my grand
   daughter.....she has a 504 plan,matter of fact I go next wednesday to
   update it for this school year.........


